netInt.graphElements

Class Node

  • java.lang.Object
    • netInt.graphElements.GraphElement
      • netInt.graphElements.Node
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Node>

    public class Node
extends GraphElement
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Node>
    This class has two predefined attributes stored in the hashMap that use these keys: id (String) and (label (String). Any other attribute is stored with the key retrieved from the graph source file, usually a graphml. *** IMPORTANT*** the attribute "id" defines the node identity therefore it must be a unique identifier
    Author:
    juan salamanca Nov 2016
